GIYANI - Health officials in Limpopo insist the situation is under control, despite confirming several cases of malaria. At least 15 people have died from the disease in the province.READ: Limpopo family searching for answers after malaria deathThe province reported over a thousand infections so far.Residents are blaming government for failing to spray mosquito repellent in the area.Officials attribute the problem to heavy rains.eNCA